HOLLYWOOD star, Tasha Smith made a mark on Nollywood practitioners when she spoiled ‘Jemeji’ star, Teniola Aladese with a prize valued at over N1 million. Smith and Aladese’s path first crossed on the stage of the 2022 Africa Magic Viewers Choice awards, when she emerged the winner of the trailblazer award on Saturday night, May 14, in Lagos, Nigeria. Smith, who was in Nigeria alongside a few Hollywood stars that attended the awards ceremony, presented the award to the rising star, whose acting, producing, and casting career in 2013.   Eldee: It’s disrespectful to credit Beyoncé for Afrobeat…     GD Harrison: There needs for more synergy among Gospel…     Portable acquires another automobile   After presenting the Trailblazer award to ‘Forbidden’ actress, Smith, who is popular for her role as Angela in Tyler Perry’s “Why did I get married,” she went on to surprise the winner and the attendees of the awards show when she announced a gift of $2,000 and free training at the Tasha Smith Acting Workshop for Aladese. Meanwhile, Aladese had won the sum of N1 million as the money prize attached to the category of award. Further investigation revealed that Tasha Smith Acting Workshop is popular for boosting actors’ confidence with classes that are specified for teens, beginners, and masterclass. From Denzel Washington to Tyler Perry, Brandy and Mary J Blige and many more have all passed through Smith’s acting workshop or worked with her at different times and in different capacities.